message.content:
1. The mean expenditure on the products among households who bought them was USD6.43.
2. 30.4% of households in the intervention clusters spent more than the mean expenditure.
3. 36.7% of households in the control clusters spent more than the mean expenditure.
4. The difference in percentage of households spending more than the mean between intervention and control clusters is -0.06.
5. The 95% confidence interval for this difference is from -0.12 to -0.01.
